 PresidentMuhammadu Buhari will make a national broadcast to Nigerians on Thursday (today) by 7am. This was made known in a press release late Wednesday, by the Special Adviser to the President on Media & Publicity, Femi Adesina. The statement said, “Television, radio stations and other electronic media outlets are enjoined to hook up to the network services of the Nigerian Television Authority and Radio Nigeria for the broadcast.” The reason for the broadcast or what would be addressed by the president was however, not stated.